  <Docs>
    <summary>Describes a single variation axis of a variable font.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontVariationAxis` describes a single variable font axis as returned by
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.VariationDesignParameters> or
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.GetVariationDesignParameters(System.Span{SkiaSharp.SKFontVariationAxis})>.
It exposes the axis tag, its minimum, default, and maximum design-space values, and
whether the axis should be hidden from the user interface.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
foreach (var axis in typeface.VariationDesignParameters)
{
    Console.WriteLine(
        $"Axis: {axis.Tag}, Range: [{axis.Min}..{axis.Max}], Default: {axis.Default}");
}
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
